<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
The species closely resembles that of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. aenea" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="aenea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">L. aenea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Simon, 1889 in having a branched embolic projection and medially inflated copulatory ducts, but it differs in having: 1) the embolus longer than the tooth of the embolic base in ventral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Male palp of Laufeia banna sp. nov., holotype A ventral B retrolateral C bulb, ventral D retrolateral. Scale bars: 0.1." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1062.72531.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/599294" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">4A, C</figureCitation>
) vs. much shorter than the tooth of the embolic base in 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. aenea" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="aenea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">L. aenea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" author="Ikeda, H" journalOrPublisher="Acta Arachnologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="37 - 43" refId="B6" refString="Ikeda, H, 1998. Spiders of the genus Laufeia (Araneae: Salticidae) from Japan. Acta Arachnologica 47: 37 - 43, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" title="Spiders of the genus Laufeia (Araneae: Salticidae) from Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" volume="47" year="1998">Ikeda 1998</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 6); 2) the retrolateral tibial apophysis is slightly curved (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Male palp of Laufeia banna sp. nov., holotype A ventral B retrolateral C bulb, ventral D retrolateral. Scale bars: 0.1." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1062.72531.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/599294" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">4A, B</figureCitation>
) vs. twisted in 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. aenea" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="aenea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">L. aenea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" author="Ikeda, H" journalOrPublisher="Acta Arachnologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="37 - 43" refId="B6" refString="Ikeda, H, 1998. Spiders of the genus Laufeia (Araneae: Salticidae) from Japan. Acta Arachnologica 47: 37 - 43, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" title="Spiders of the genus Laufeia (Araneae: Salticidae) from Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" volume="47" year="1998">Ikeda 1998</bibRefCitation>
: figs 5, 6); 3) the atrium has a pair of arc-shaped, anterolateral ridges (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Female paratype and male holotype of Laufeia banna sp. nov. A epigyne, ventral B vulva, dorsal C holotype habitus, dorsal D ventral E female paratype habitus, dorsal F holotype carapace, frontal G holotype left chelicera, posterior. Scale bars: 0.1 (A, B, G); 0.5 (C-E); 0.2 (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1062.72531.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/599295" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">5A</figureCitation>
) vs. only one anterior ridge in 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. aenea" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="aenea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">L. aenea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" author="Ikeda, H" journalOrPublisher="Acta Arachnologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="37 - 43" refId="B6" refString="Ikeda, H, 1998. Spiders of the genus Laufeia (Araneae: Salticidae) from Japan. Acta Arachnologica 47: 37 - 43, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" title="Spiders of the genus Laufeia (Araneae: Salticidae) from Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" volume="47" year="1998">Ikeda 1998</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7); 4) the copulatory openings are elongated and slit-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Female paratype and male holotype of Laufeia banna sp. nov. A epigyne, ventral B vulva, dorsal C holotype habitus, dorsal D ventral E female paratype habitus, dorsal F holotype carapace, frontal G holotype left chelicera, posterior. Scale bars: 0.1 (A, B, G); 0.5 (C-E); 0.2 (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1062.72531.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/599295" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">5A</figureCitation>
) vs. oval in 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. aenea" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="aenea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">L. aenea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" author="Ikeda, H" journalOrPublisher="Acta Arachnologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="37 - 43" refId="B6" refString="Ikeda, H, 1998. Spiders of the genus Laufeia (Araneae: Salticidae) from Japan. Acta Arachnologica 47: 37 - 43, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" title="Spiders of the genus Laufeia (Araneae: Salticidae) from Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.47.37" volume="47" year="1998">Ikeda 1998</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Male</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Male palp of Laufeia banna sp. nov., holotype A ventral B retrolateral C bulb, ventral D retrolateral. Scale bars: 0.1." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1062.72531.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/599294" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Female paratype and male holotype of Laufeia banna sp. nov. A epigyne, ventral B vulva, dorsal C holotype habitus, dorsal D ventral E female paratype habitus, dorsal F holotype carapace, frontal G holotype left chelicera, posterior. Scale bars: 0.1 (A, B, G); 0.5 (C-E); 0.2 (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1062.72531.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/599295" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">5C, D, F, G</figureCitation>
). Total length 2.11. Carapace 1.04 long, 0.79 wide. Abdomen 0.88 long, 0.83 wide. Clypeus 0.01 high. Eye sizes and inter-distances: AME 0.22, ALE 0.14, PLE 0.13, AERW 0. 68, PERW 0.63, EFL 0.42. Legs: I 1.50 (0.53, 0.55, 0.21, 0.21), II 1.36 (0.45, 0.48, 0.21, 0.22), III 1.46 (0.50, 0.50, 0.23, 0.23), IV 1.59 (0.50, 0.58, 0.28, 0.23). Carapace red-brown, darker laterally and at bases of PLEs and PMEs, covered with sparse, thin, white setae, slightly denser on face. Fovea almost round. Chelicerae red to dark brown, with 2 promarginal teeth and 1 retromarginal fissident with 2 cusps. Endites broadened mediodistally, pale ental margins. Labium linguiform, paler distally. Sternum somewhat shield shaped. Legs brown to dark brown, except tarsi yellow, covered with sparse, white setae. Abdomen almost spherical, dorsum red-brown, with several transverse dotted lines posteriorly, covered by sparse, pale, thin setae; venter brown, with 4 longitudinal dotted lines.
</paragraph>
